body.p:
The CSS that hides the topicrefs at level 2 or
      more::root[only-chapters-in-toc='yes'] *[class ~= "toc/toc"] 
         > *[class ~= "map/topicref"]> *[class ~= "map/topicref"] {
  display:none;
}The :root[a|only-chapters-in-toc='yes'] selector makes the rule
      activate only when the attribute is set.
